article.headline: Lipscomb 70, Florida Gulf Coast 56
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. (AP) -- Michael Lusk had 16 points as Lipscomb beat Florida Gulf Coast 70-56 on Thursday night. Lusk had four 3-pointers for the Bisons (3-5, 9-13). LaKory Daniels and Eddie Ard each had 14 points. Landon Adler had 14 points and 11 rebounds off the bench for Florida Gulf Coast (8-14, 4-4), which saw its three-game conference winning streak end. It was Adler's sixth double-double of the season. Lipcomb used a 14-0 run to take a 20-6 lead. Adler's 3-pointer cut the deficit to 31-28 but the Bisons responded with a 12-0 run over the end of the first half and start of second half. Delvin Franklin added 12 points for the Eagles. Lipscomb led 36-28 at halftime.
